                    <span>I hadn't realized that Mr Pietrek is something of a legend.  I<br>simply set out to find a decent book that would (un)cover <br>some of the "secret" things about Win32 programming that were<br>tripping me up.  Not only did I find answers, I found other<br>things to steer around.  It's a good book, it's readable, and<br>even a bit funny.  I'd buy it again, most certainly.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">A must have.   I keep coming back to the excellant reference</div>
