                    </div>
                    <span>There are very few books that I have gotten this much wealth of information out of.  Matt spent a lot of time researching it, reverse engineering windows 95 to see how it works.  I would gladly pay 10 times  the sales price.   I found the in depth coverage of the PE (win95 EXEs)  file format much better than anything microsoft has to offer.  Also, many  people will find the section on how to "inject" DLLs into another  process space very useful for all sorts things.  The coverage of how  exceptions are handled is very good.  All of the information in the book is  still valid today even though it came out in 95.  Anyone writing a  debugger, compiler, profiler, or system tool will find this book useful.   Let's hope Matt writes another book!</span>
                  
